cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for 3D keypoint detection using deep learning, specifically a deep neural network with sparse autoencoder. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with analyzing and understanding 3D mesh models. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG), and the fact that it deals with 3D models suggests it could also fall under graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the use of autoencoders suggests it could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
